  <body>
    <section name="Go to a Document type">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to get to a screen to manipulate a particular document type.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=445;
    bottompx=300;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M9/inars/documenttype_tab.png" alt='documenttype tab screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
    <p>
     Opened the <a href='../../contributors/concepts/card.html'>card</a> for the document
     type 'upcoming', which is a document type in the namespace
      'sar'. For the document type, the actions '<a href='../concepts/edit_mode.html'>edit</a>' and 'Copy' are possible.
      The 'upcoming' document type is already filled by a structure definition containing the fields:
      Date of happening, Title, Indoors?, Recurring? and Description. Except for Description, they
      all are mandatory (this is shown by the * signs).
     </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    While a <a href='./goto_namespace.html'>namespace is selected</a>,
    click on a document type name in the list at middle right.
   </p>

